citations:
    citation-adwd-the-dragontamer:
        source: source-adwd
        properties:
            locator: "The Dragontamer"
            text_from_source: "Quentyn turned and threw his left arm across his face to shield his eyes from the furnace wind. Rhaegal, he reminded himself, the green one is Rhaegal. When he raised his whip, he saw that the lash was burning. His hand as well. All of him, all of him was burning. Oh, he thought. Then he began to scream."
            accessed: "2026-03-06"
        notes: "Quentyn Martell POV. In the predawn hours, Quentyn, Gerris Drinkwater, and Archibald Yronwood disguise themselves as Brazen Beasts using costumes supplied by the Tattered Prince (a bull mask for Arch, a lion for Quentyn, an ape for Gerris). They gain access to the Great Pyramid using the day's password 'dog.' They enter the dragon pit where Rhaegal and Viserion are kept chained. The plan: feed the dragons, chain them in their torpor, transport them to a waiting ship. Caggo Corpsekiller and Pretty Meris of the Windblown assist. Rhaegal's collar shows broken chains — three feet of broken chain dangling. Viserion has excavated a nest in the thick pyramid wall. The four Brazen Beast guards at the pit door do not accept the password, and a fight erupts — the basilisk-masked serjeant is killed by Archibald's warhammer, two locusts killed by Gerris and a crossbow bolt. One yields; Caggo decapitates him. Viserion breaks free toward the door; a Windblown crossbowman fires a bolt into Viserion's neck. Viserion kills the crossbowman (burns his face, tears his neck). The Windblown flee. Quentyn attempts to cow Viserion with a whip — Viserion hisses but does not submit. Rhaegal attacks from behind. Quentyn is engulfed in dragonflame from Rhaegal. He begins to scream. The chapter ends with Quentyn burning alive. Both Rhaegal and Viserion escape their prison."
